content:
Specify who can create apps and edit and delete datasets and dashboards by making Analytics Studio invisible to Analytics Tab users on a per profile basis.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To restrict access to the Analytics Studio within the Analytics tab:

From Setup, enter App Manager.
Open the Analytics Studio menu and select Edit.
Clear the check from the Visible column in the Assign to Profiles section for the profile you want to restrict.

Although disabling visibility removes UI links to Analytics Studio, any URL to the Studio version of an asset always opens it in Studio. The Studio version URL is available in the Share dialog and provided in notification and subscription emails. 

Access to Analytics Studio from embedded dashboards is controlled through the component's attributes.
title: Restricting Access to CRM Analytics Studio
